subsection.def:
alteration (改動),
                for the purposes of the definition of constructed, means any repair,
                alteration or modification that is of a major character; (L.N. 256 of 2018)

paragraph.content:
construction identifiable with the ship begins and assembly of the ship
                        has commenced comprising at least 50 tonnes or 1% of the estimated mass of
                        all structural material, whichever is less;

assembly of that ship has commenced comprising at least 50 tonnes or 1%
                        of the estimated mass of all structural material, whichever is
                        less;

Resolution 1 of the Conference of Contracting Governments to the
                        International Convention for the Safety of Life at Sea, 1974 on the Global
                        Maritime Distress and Safety System adopted on 9 November 1988;

subsection.def:
suitable
                    (適合) in relation to material means approved
                by the Director as suitable for the purpose for which it is used;

paragraph.content:
in ships of 50 metres but less than 61 metres in length, from the forward
                    bulkhead of the machinery space to the collision bulkhead or as near to that
                    bulkhead as is practicable;

in ships of 61 metres but less than 76 metres in length, from the collision
                    bulkhead to the afterpeak bulkhead or as near to those bulkheads as is
                    practicable, but not necessarily in the machinery space;

subparagraph.content:
0.030 metre-radian between the angles of heel of 30 degrees and 40
                        degrees or such lesser angle as is referred to in subparagraph
                        (ii);

paragraph.content:
In every ship designed or adapted for the carriage of goods vehicles and accompanying personnel, hinged, rolling or sliding watertight doors may be fitted at any level in watertight bulkheads dividing cargo spaces intended for such vehicles, if the total number of passengers, including the personnel accompanying the goods vehicles, which the ship is intended to carry does not exceed 12 +
A 25
;

for a passenger ship constructed on or after 1 September 1984 and
                        before 1 July 1998—has the meaning given by regulation 1(2);
                        or

subparagraph.content:
the pumping arrangements required shall take account of the
                            requirements for any fixed pressure water-spraying fire-extinguishing
                            system;

paragraph.content:
where the deepest subdivision load line coincides or nearly coincides with
                    the fresh water line, the subdivision marking C.1 or C may be indicated on the
                    forward side of the grid;

be driven by internal combustion machinery with an independent fuel supply,
                    having a flash point of not less than 43oC (Closed Cup
                    Test);

be capable of supplying the emergency electrical load without being
                    recharged, whilst maintaining the voltage of the battery throughout the required
                    discharge period within 12% of its nominal voltage;

be arranged to supply automatically the services required by paragraphs (c)
                    and (d) for at least half an hour in the event of the failure of either the main
                    or emergency source of electrical power;

flexible oil pressure pipes of suitable materials and construction may be
                    permitted by the Director provided that their location is in accordance with
                    paragraph (a);

subsection.content:
every valve used in connection with the oil fuel installation shall be so
                designed and constructed as to prevent the cover of the valve chest being slackened
                back or loosened when the valve is operated;

paragraph.content:
the speed, direction of thrust and, if variable, the pitch of the propeller
                    shall be fully controllable from the navigating bridge under any sailing
                    condition including manoeuvring;

propulsion machinery movements selected at the navigating bridge shall be
                    indicated in the main machinery control room or at the manoeuvring platform as
                    appropriate;

the main propulsion machinery shall be provided with an emergency stopping
                    device, located on the navigating bridge, which shall be independent of the
                    controls otherwise required by this regulation;

the number of automatic and consecutive attempts which fail to start any
                    internal combustion propulsion engine shall be limited so as to maintain
                    sufficient air pressure for further attempts under local control;

there shall be provided above the bulkhead deck at least two means of
                    escape from each space bounded by main vertical zone bulkheads or from each
                    similarly restricted space or group of spaces;

subparagraph.content:
stairways shall not exceed 3.5 metres in vertical rise without the
                        provision of a landing and shall not have an angle of inclination greater
                        than 45 degrees;

paragraph.content:
from the conning position the horizontal field of vision shall extend over
                    an arc of at least 225o, that is from right ahead to not less than
                        22.5o abaft the beam on either side of the ship;

from the main steering position the horizontal field of vision shall extend
                    over an arc from right ahead to at least 60o on each side of the
                    ship;

subparagraph.content:
to help avoid reflections, the bridge front windows shall be inclined
                        from the vertical plane top out, at an angle of not less than 10o
                        and not more than 25o;

paragraph.content:
additional subdivision is provided in way of the step to maintain
                            the same measure of safety as that secured by a plane bulkhead;
                            or

subparagraph.content:
for a ro/ro passenger ship—throughout the ship’s length;
                                    (L.N. 256 of
                                2018)

for lifeboats which are arranged to be launched fully
                                    loaded from the stowed position, the maximum heeling moment
                                    during launching shall be taken;

persons not in the life-saving appliances which are swung
                                    out shall not provide either additional heeling or righting
                                    moment;

life-saving appliances on the side of the ship opposite to
                                    the side to which the ship has heeled shall be assumed to be in
                                    a stowed position;

the area applicable shall be the projected lateral area of
                                    the ship above the waterline corresponding to the intact
                                    condition;

the moment arm shall be the vertical distance from a point
                                    at one half of the mean draught corresponding to the intact condition to
                                    the centre of gravity of the lateral area;

paragraph.content:
in the case of symmetrical flooding there shall be a positive
                            residual metacentric height of at least 50 millimetres as calculated by
                            the constant displacement method;
